EZBOB
Raises
&pound;3
Million
in
Private
Equity
Investment
By
David
Penn
Posted
on
April
3,
2015
Categories:
EZBOB
<!--<div
class="sharing">
-->
U.K.-based
SME
lender
EZBOB
has
raised
£3
million
in
new
capital
courtesy
of
a
private
equity
investment.
The
investment
takes
the
company&#8217;s
total
capital
to
more
than
£16
million
(more
than
$23
million
USD),
including
a
£7
million
debt-financing
round
in
February
2014.
EZBOB
made
headlines
this
spring
with
its
partnership
with
online
Chinese
marketplace
Alibaba.
A
loan
guarantee
agreement
with
the
European
Investment
Fund
(EIF)
in
March
enabled
EZBOB
to
increase
its
loan
volumes
by
up
to
£40
million
over
the
next
two
years.
EZBOB
acquired
Everline,
Wonga&#8217;s
small
business
financing
unit,
in
February.
A
two-time
Finovate
alum,
EZBOB
last
appeared
on
the
Finovate
stage
as
part
of
FinovateEurope
2014
conference.
The
company
was
founded
in
November
2011
by
Tomer
Guriel,
CEO,
and
Sharone
Perlstein,
business
development,
and
is
headquartered
in
London.
